{
  "stem": "3690.1",
  "chunk_idx": 2,
  "model": "openai/gpt-oss-120b",
  "elapsed_s": 3.7,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 13,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "And they came over from the border towns, for like from Poland, so they started take the Polish people, like the Polish people they came in.",
      "word_count": 26
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 14,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "So they, they grabbed them and, and they tried to deport them.",
      "word_count": 12
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 14,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "We never know what happened to them because they took those people and we never know where they taken them.",
      "word_count": 20
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 14,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "And not only they take the person, but they took the whole families.",
      "word_count": 13
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 14,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "The wives and the children, and sometimes even if the in-laws wanted to go with them, they took them, even the in-laws.",
      "word_count": 22
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 14,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "And these were the Hungarians who did that?",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 15,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "That, that was done by the Hungarians, right.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 16,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "In 1939 when the war started, the, the Jews were kind of depressed.",
      "word_count": 13
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 16,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "They-- you couldn't go in the streets very well, because you heard remarks, call you Jews should go home, or Jew go to Palestine, and stuff like that.",
      "word_count": 28
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 16,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "And it was kind of, kind of depressed.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 16,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "You weren't, you weren't free to move around like you used to.",
      "word_count": 12
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 16,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "So you had to be, you know, cautious and careful not to make waves to get in trouble.",
      "word_count": 18
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 17,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "We seen-- the first time we seen German troops was in 1942.",
      "word_count": 12
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 17,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "And they, they-- but there weren't much German troops because the Hungarian Gendarme was kind of cahoots with the German soldiers and the German troops.",
      "word_count": 25
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 17,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "And they took over the town like the, the running of the town, or the, the execution of the people who they wanted to deport or to get first.",
      "word_count": 29
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 17,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "And it started getting worse and worse all the time.",
      "word_count": 10
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 18,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "Not in the beginning, no.",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 18,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "Later on, it became that the Jews weren't allowed to go shopping in the town, or only stay in certain areas like a ghetto.",
      "word_count": 24
    }
  ],
